description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Registered Nurse to work within the Acute Medical Unit (AMU). This post will be crucial in helping us provide and deliver safe, effective, high quality patient care. Candidates are required to hold a valid 1st level registration with the Nursing and Midwifery Council.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking enthusiastic, highly motivated individuals to be part of an innovative, multidisciplinary team involved in acute medicine. They must demonstrate organisational skills, research and evidence based practice. The successful candidate will possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills with a good understanding of admission and discharge processes to ensure effective patient flow.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role will actively support the senior ward sister and nurse coordinator in the delivery of a high quality service to patients and their families in an ever changing and challenging acute clinical environment supported by a practice development nurse to provide professional development pathways within acute medicine. For further information and to hear of the benefits available surrounding the areas please contact Ward Managers:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Kate Humphris/Jess Confaloni on 0300422 8584 / 8272 (GRH) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;kate.humphris@nhs.net or jess.confaloni@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
